Crispy chicken and potato sticks 🍟 Ingredients 4 large potatoes ( peeled and cut into cubes ) 1/3 cup freshly grated parmesan cheese 1/2 cup shredded boiled chicken 2 tbsp corn flour 3 tbsp all purpose flour Salt to taste 1 tsp black pepper 1/2 tbsp garlic powder 1 tbsp cajun seasoning Oil for frying Method: Peel, cut and boil the potatoes. Mash the potatoes until silky and smooth , add finely chopped chicken and grated parmesan cheese. Add corn flour,ap flour,salt black pepper garlic powder and cajun seasoning. Mix well and place the mixture in a zip lock bag. Flatten the mixture with a rolling pin until evenly distributed. Freeze the mixture for 30-40 minutes until set. Take out the mixture and cut it into fries shape. Fry the potatoes on medium to high heat until crispy and golden brown. Garnish with more parmesan cheese. Serve with your favorite dipping sauce and enjoy ! #frenchfries #chickenfries #potatoes #ramadanrecipes #recipes

How to eat balut! 🥚 Balut aka hột vịt lộn is a fertilized duck egg. It’s a delicacy & popular street food in Southeast Asia. In Vietnam, the eggs are boiled & eaten with muối tiêu chanh (salt, pepper, lime) & rau răm (Vietnamese coriander). I love the liquid inside the egg & the yolk! It tastes like a richer chicken broth & hard boiled egg but with a yolkier flavor. The duck itself is not my fave tbh. I call this my magic potion 🥰 Elderberry: is a natural remedy to help boost the immune system and prevent or reduce the duration and severity of cold and flu symptoms in children (+1 year old) and adults. Ginger: anti-inflammatory, immune booster, pain relief. Turmeric: anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties. Cinnamon: anti-bacterial properties. Lemon: Vitamin C relieves congestion. Honey: Soothing sore Throat, suppress cough. Here is the recipe 💕 Ingredients: 1 cup dried elderberries 4 cups water 1 inch fresh ginger, peeled 1 lemon, sliced 3 cinnamon sticks 1 teaspoon ground turmeric 1 cup honey (local unfiltered honey is better) Instructions: In a large pot, combine the elderberries, water, ginger, lemon, cinnamon sticks, and turmeric. Bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to low and let simmer for about 45 minutes, or until the liquid has reduced by half. Remove from heat and let cool for a few minutes. Then, strain the mixture through a fine-mesh strainer into a clean bowl or jar, let the liquid cool to room temperature. Stir in the honey until completely dissolved. Transfer the syrup to a clean jar or bottle and store in the refrigerator for up to 3-4 weeks. adults may take 1 tablespoon (15 mL) of elderberry syrup per day, while children over the age of 1 year may take 1/2 to 1 teaspoon (2.5-5 mL) per day. However, it’s always best to consult with a healthcare provider before. Note: it is not recommended to give elderberry syrup to children under the age of 1 year. #elderberrysyrup #momhacks #momlife #naturalremedies #elderberry #elderberrysyruprecipe #coldandfluseason
